# Int.toChar constructs a UTF-16 code unit

Regression for `portable-codepoint-string-construction`: `n.toChar` builds a Char
from an Int code point (65 -> 'A', 8364 -> '€'), and Chars stringify as their
character, not their numeric code. INT/JVM/JS agree.

```scalascript
val a = 65.toChar
val b = 8364.toChar
println(a.toString + b.toString)
println(List(65, 66, 67).map(_.toChar).mkString)
```
